# Force LF line endings for all text files, regardless of the cloning
# environment's core.autocrlf setting. Without this, a fresh clone on
# Windows with the common core.autocrlf=true default corrupts every bash
# script with CRLF line endings, breaking them outright (e.g.
# "$'\r': command not found") - discovered when merging Phase 1 into
# master produced exactly that failure in this checkout.
* text=auto eol=lf
